Program: Discovery
Title: Optical astronomy
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrz5y
Last Broadcast Date: 06 June 2006
Discovering the world of high-energy astronomy with ultraviolet, X-ray and gamma-ray telescopes. The programme is presented by former NASA astronaut and MIT professor of astronomy Jeffrey Hoffman. He looks at why only certain types of light can be seen from space.